<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Using a configuration array to wire up a global logger is currently obtuse.  Writers construct signatures vary too much to be practical.  Here's what I want to do in my autoload/global.php:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
array(
    'logger' =&gt; array(
        'writers' =&gt; array(
            'Stream' =&gt; array(
                'streamOrUrl' =&gt; 'log/application.log',
            ),
        ),
    ),
);
</code></pre>

<p>Now, I can write a custom Factory just for that Writer.  But, as soon as I try to make it generic for any writer, I run into signature hell.  I haven't even begun to try to config filters or formatters.</p>

<p>See: <a href="http://logging.apache.org/log4php/docs/configuration.html">http://logging.apache.org/log4php/docs/…</a></p>

